 It is not entirely clear, at least to me, what Lord Carnwath understood UTJ Southern to have meant by the words which he emphasised or, therefore, why he emphasised them.  But if, as I assume, he was intending to approve those words it would seem to be on the basis that they were to the same effect as his observation in para. 23 that the public interest in the deportation of foreign criminals affords the context for measuring what degree of harshness is justifiable. 
